value.value: A response indicating that something occurs with the same frequency or intensity as previously.
The presence of a calculus in the ureter of the kidney; this is most often composed of mineral salts and proteins.
Acid-sensing ion channel 2 (512 aa, ~58 kDa) is encoded by the human ASIC2 gene. This protein is involved in both synaptic transmission and cation transport.
Abnormally low urine output.
Absence of urine output.
A recombinant chemokine of human lymphotactin which is produced by activated progenitor T cells and characterized by specific chemotactic activity for lymphocytes. (NCI)
This gene plays a role in lipid binding.

Human ACBD6 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q25.1 and is approximately 228 kb in length. This allele, which encodes acyl-CoA-binding domain-containing protein 6, is involved in binding to acylated coenzyme A.
The visible presence of blood in the urine.
Acyl-CoA-binding domain-containing protein 6 (282 aa, ~31 kDa) is encoded by the human ACBD6 gene. This protein plays a role in acyl-coenzyme A binding.
A response indicating a certainty that something occurs with little frequency or intensity.
The presence of myoglobin in the urine.

label.value: A Great Deal of the Time

value.value: A response indicating that something happens or happened much of the time.
Abnormally high level of calcium in the urine.
Abnormally low level of citrate in the urine.
A response indicating that something happens or happened infrequently.
A subjective answer of very strong agreement.
A response indicating that something happens or happened most of the time.
A response indicating that something happens or happened nearly all of the time.
A response indicating that something happens or happened frequently.
A severe hypersensitivity-like reaction occurring during dialysis due to exposure to the dialysis membrane.
A response indicating that an individual does not take as much care as they should.

label.value: May Not Take as Much Care

value.value: A response indicating that an individual may not take as much care as they should.
A crack or break in a dialysis catheter caused by material weakness or mechanical compression.
A response indicating that an individual takes as much care as they always have.
A subjective answer of disagreement.
A response indicating that something occurs with less frequency or intensity as previously.
A response indicating a certainty that something occurs with much less frequency or intensity as previously.
An obstruction of a vessel caused by a detached fragment of an indwelling dialysis catheter.
A local or systemic infection associated with the use of a dialysis catheter.
A local or systemic infection associated with the use of a hemodialysis catheter.
A local or systemic infection associated with the use of a peritoneal dialysis catheter.
Local infection involving the subcutaneously tunneled portion of a dialysis catheter.
Local infection at the dialysis catheter exit site.
The presence of bacteria in the blood caused by an infected hemodialysis catheter.

An inflammatory form of programmed cell death characterized by caspase-dependent formation of plasma-membrane pores, which leads to pathological changes in osmotic potential that ultimately result in cellular lysis and release of pro-inflammatory cytokines. It occurs most frequently following infection with intracellular pathogens, but also has a role in tumor suppression and the initiation of anti-tumor immune responses, as well as in autoimmune and cardiovascular diseases.
A family of plasma membrane resident proteins that hydrolyze ATP to facilitate the transport of calcium ions out of the cytoplasm into the extracellular space.
This gene plays a role in myosin function.

Human MPRIP wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p11.2 and is approximately 175 kb in length. This allele, which encodes myosin phosphatase Rho-interacting protein, is involved in the modulation of myosin phosphorylation.
Myosin phosphatase Rho-interacting protein (1025 aa, ~117 kDa) is encoded by the human MPRIP gene. This protein plays a role in the recruitment of myosin phosphatase to the cytoskeleton.
This gene is involved in both DNA replication and sister chromatid cohesion.

Human WAPL wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 10q23.2 and is approximately 87 kb in length. This allele, which encodes wings apart-like protein homolog, plays a role in mitosis, meiosis and DNA replication.
Wings apart-like protein homolog (1190 aa, ~133 kDa) is encoded by the human WAPL gene. This protein is involved in meiosis, mitosis and DNA replication.
This gene plays a role in clathrin-mediated endocytosis.

Human SYNJ1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 21q22.2 and is approximately 99 kb in length. This allele, which encodes synaptojanin-1 protein, is involved in the modulation of clathrin-coated vesicle endocytosis. Mutation of the gene is associated with early onset Parkinson disease 20.
Synaptojanin-1 (1573 aa, ~173 kDa) is encoded by the human SYNJ1 gene. This protein plays a role in vesicle endocytosis.
